    <div class="contain">
        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Historical Significance</h2>
                <p>
                    Pakhala Dibasa, celebrated on March 20th, honors Pakhala—a fermented rice dish soaked in water, a
                    staple in Odisha for centuries. Rooted in rural life, it reflects the state’s ingenuity in creating
                    cooling, nutritious meals suited to its climate. The day unites Odias worldwide in pride for their
                    culinary legacy.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Cultural Highlights</h2>
                <p>
                    The celebration features community feasts, cooking contests, and cultural programs showcasing Odia
                    traditions. Songs and dances accompany the sharing of Pakhala recipes, passed down through generations.
                    It’s a joyous tribute to simplicity and identity, bringing families and friends together in festivity.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Food and Cuisine</h2>
                <p>
                    Pakhala takes center stage, served with sides like fried fish, mashed potatoes (aloo bharta), and
                    sautéed greens. Variations include curd or buttermilk Pakhala, spiced with local flavors. Stalls and
                    homes offer this refreshing dish, paired with pickles and papad, delighting food lovers everywhere.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Shopping Experience</h2>
                <p>
                    During Pakhala Dibasa, local markets sell clay pots, traditional utensils, and spices used in preparing
                    the dish. Vendors offer packaged Pakhala kits and recipe books, perfect for enthusiasts. It’s a chance
                    to grab authentic Odia kitchenware and ingredients that elevate the experience.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Festive Atmosphere</h2>
                <p>
                    On March 20th, Odisha buzzes with a festive spirit—households, restaurants, and public spaces host
                    Pakhala feasts. Social media floods with photos and recipes, while cultural events amplify the cheer.
                    The day radiates warmth and unity, celebrating a dish that defines Odia resilience and taste.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

